  "text": "Facial Micro-Expressions (MEs) are spontaneous, involuntary facial movements when a person experiences an emotion but deliberately or unconsciously attempts to conceal his or her genuine emotions [CITATION_1] - [CITATION_2] . MEs are more likely to occur in high-risk environments because there are more risks to show true emotions [CITATION_3] . Recently, automatic facial ME analysis has attracted increasing attention of affective computing researchers and psychologists because of its potential applications such as clinical diagnosis, business negotiation, interrogations, and security [CITATION_4] , [CITATION_5] . The study",
